### Describe the bug
(This is a new attempt to describe one issue in https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/30534)

I have multiple third-party (i.e. I cannot modify) components that take multiple `RenderFragment` parameters. I will use a simplified example with only two RenderFragments:
```c#
@*Foo.razor*@
@if (Block1!=null)
{
    @Block1
} else {
    <...some other stuff...>
}
@if (Block2!=null)
{
    @Block2
} else {
    <...some other stuff...>
}
@code{
    [Parameter]
    public RenderFragment Block1 { get; set; }
    [Parameter]
    public RenderFragment Block2 { get; set; }
}
```
I want to be able to set each `RenderFragement` to have child content conditionally (based on some state) and `null` otherwise.

What I tried.

1)
```c#
<Foo>
    <Block1>
        @if (condition1)
        {
            <..some data..>
        }
    </Block1>
    <Block2>
        @if (condition2)
        {
            <..some data..>
        }
    </Block2>
</Foo>
```
But this doesn't work, as empty `RenderFragment`s are not the same as `null`.

2)
```c#
<Foo>
    @if (condition1)
    {
        <Block1>
            <..some data..>
        </Block1>
    }
    @if (condition2)
    {
        <Block2>
            <..some data..>
        </Block2>
    }
</Foo>
```
doesn't compile: `RZ9996 Unrecognized child content inside component 'Foo'. The component 'Foo' accepts child content through the following top-level items: 'Block'.`

3)
```c#
@if (!condition1 && !condition2)
{
    <Foo />
} else if (condition1 && !condition2)
{
    <Foo>
        <Block1>
            <..some data..>
        </Block1>
    </Foo>
} else if (!condition1 && condition2)
{
    <Foo>
        <Block2>
            <..some data..>
        </Block2>
    </Foo>
} else //if (condition1 && condition2)
    <Foo>
        <Block1>
            <..some data..>
        </Block1>
        <Block2>
            <..some data..>
        </Block2>
    </Foo>
}
```
works, has a lot of code duplication **and doesn't scale well**! It's O(2^N). This is just a simple example with 2 block = 4 possibilities. With 3 blocks its 8, with 4 -> 16 etc.

4)
```c#
<Foo Block1=@(condition1?<..some data...>:null) Block2=@(condition2?<...some data...>:null) />
```
This compiles, but doesn't work then either of the conditions are false: It will throw a `ArgumentException: Delegate to an instance method cannot have null 'this'.`

I consider the last code the best option, however it doesn't work due to a limitation in the razor source generator. Details on that can be found in https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/30534

